 Brown as mayor of Oakland) <br/> KQED (TV) || Producer, Writer\n|-\n| 2002-2008 || ''[[Frontline (TV series)|Frontline]]''<br/>\"Frontline World\" (TV) 30 episodes || Series Editor, Senior Producer\n|-\n| 2004 || ''[[Frontline (TV series)|Frontline]]''<br/> ''Diet Wars'' (TV) || Host\n|-\n| 2005 || ''The Sixties: The Years That Shaped<br/>a Generation'' (TV) || Co-Producer\n|-\n| 2007 ||  ''[[Frontline (TV series)|Frontline]]''<br/>''News War: What's Happening to the News'' (TV) || Producer, Co-Writer\n|-\n| 2010 & 2012 || \"[[Sound Tracks: Music Without Borders]]\" <br/> (TV) PBS || Executive Producer\n|-\n| 2011 ||  \"[[The Price of Sex]]\"<br/> (film) || Executive Producer\n|-\n| 2013 || \"[[To Kill a Sparrow]]\"<br/> (short film) || Senior Producer\n|-\n| 2015 || \"[[Daisy and Max]]\"<br/> Al Jazeera America || Executive Producer\n|-\n| 2018 || \"[[Moscone: A Legacy of Change]]\" (TV) PBS || Writer\n|-\n| 2019 || \"[[Bay Area Revelations: Loma Prieta Earthquake, 30 Years Later]]\" (TV) || Co-Producer, Co-Writer\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|id=0847972|name=Stephen Talbot}}\n*[https://www.pbs.org/show/sound-tracks/ Official PBS site for \"Sound Tracks: Music Without Borders\"]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/soundtracksqh \"Sound Tracks Presents Quick Hits\" YouTube Channel]\n*[https://www.pbs.org/soundtracks/  \"Sound Tracks: Music Without Borders\" website]\n*[https://www.pbs.org/frontlineworld/ \"Frontline World\" website]\n*[https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/  \"Frontline\" website]\n*[http://priceofsex.org/ \"Price of Sex\" film website]\n*[https://www.revealnews.org/author/stephen-talbot/ \"Reveal News / Center for Investigative Reporting]\n*[https://www.kqed.org/forum/201205171030/remembering-carlos-fuentes KQED interview on the death of writer Carlos Fuentes. 2012]\n*[https://www.kqed.org/forum/2010101868311/documentary-highlights-impact-of-late-sf-mayor-george-moscone KQED interview on the life an